<img class="aligncenter wp-image-1307828 size-full" src="https://i0.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/NIMC.jpg?resize=640%2C336&#038;ssl=1" alt="NIN enrolment" width="640" height="336" srcset="https://i0.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/NIMC.jpg?w=764&amp;ssl=1 764w, https://i0.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/NIMC.jpg?resize=300%2C157&amp;ssl=1 300w, https://i0.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/NIMC.jpg?resize=58%2C30&amp;ssl=1 58w, https://i0.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/NIMC.jpg?resize=260%2C136&amp;ssl=1 260w, https://i0.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/NIMC.jpg?resize=200%2C105&amp;ssl=1 200w, https://i0.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/12/NIMC.jpg?resize=560%2C294&amp;ssl=1 560w" sizes="(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px" data-recalc-dims="1" /> The National Identity Management Commission (NIMC) has commenced the enrolment of foreign diplomats in Nigeria. This was contained in a statement signed by Mr Kayode Adegoke, Head, Corporate Communications of NIN, in Abuja. The Minister of Communications and Digital Economy, Dr Isa Pantami, in his bid to ensure seamless enrolment of all diplomats in the country for the purpose of the ongoing NIN-SIM linkage and other needs, directed the setting up of the enrolment center at the Ministry of Foreign Affairs, Abuja. The enrolment of the diplomats started on Monday, Jan. 18. “Also, the NIMC wishes to assure members of the general public that all hands are on deck to ensure the enrolment of all Nigerians and legal residents into the National Identity Database,” he said. (NAN) Vanguard News Nigeria The Minister of Communications and Digital Economy, Dr Isa Pantami, has approved the setting up of a National Identity Number (NIN), Enrolment Centre at the Federal Ministry of Foreign Affairs, Abuja. January 17, 2021 In "News" By Emmanuel Elebeke The Director General/CEO National Identity 